@node About "About Time Prefs"

	@{b}About TimePrefs. @{ub}

This is a simple little program that I wrote one day when I was extremely bored. 

I and many others dislike the Topaz-8 look when it comes to the standard preferences programs. The original programs that the old C= made aren't even font sensitive which makes them rather ugly on a 21" monitor (I wish I had one 8). Yet there are some people that see nothing wrong with Topaz-8 and think we're all crazy. I would guess that these people are probably still using Workbench 1.3 in a non-interlaced environment 8). (BTW. I know Topaz-8 got a face-lift - post 1.3) Well we could go on forever...

The program performs in much the same way as the original Time preference program but it utilises features of my 'everyday.library' and has some further options not found in the old C= program.

If you are going to use the Everyday Organiser system then it is advisable to use this program because it informs Alarmist and On-Time when the date and time have changed.

The main advantage of this program is that it uses @{"MUI" link Everyday:Introduction.guide/MUI_Register}.

Mathew Wilson

