@endnode

@node Features "Time Prefs Features"

	@{b}FEATURES@{ub}

The program's interface is much the same as the original C= program with a few modifications. Its all pretty straight forward and I won't bore you with an explanation of what you already know. However I'll just mention a few things.

The string gadget 'Date:' enables you to manually type in the date using any of the valid forms explained in the documentation of my progam On-Time. The format of this string cam be set within the On-Time configuration.

The calendar is Locale sensitive of course.

Unlike the C= Time preferences program, this version has the Edit menu that contains the Last Saved and Restore options. These commands are usually used in reference to actual preference files stored in the ENV: and ENVARC: drawers. Since the time is is not stored in a file 8) I think C= saw no need for these options. Well, I included them anyway as they instead make reference to the Battery Clock.

Last Saved will re-read the settings in the Battery Clock, displaying them in the interface.

Restore  will re-read the 'operational counter timer' of the computer and display the settings in the interface.

When you select either Save or Use, TimePrefs will send ARexx messages to Alarmist and OnTime to update.

Well, that's all there is to it.
@endnode

@node History "History"

TimePrefs is distributed with the Everyday Organiser package. The following release dates correspond to EO releases.

· @{b}v2.00@{ub} - Sixth Release (1st April 1997)

   - 100% recompiled with SAS/C 6.57.
   - Now uses EO private external custom classes.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

· @{b}v1.30@{ub} - Fourth Release (31st August 1996)

   - Some changes made to some ARexx commands that it sends to communicate with On-Time.
   - Now reads global date format preferences set with On-Time.
   - Program has not been incorporated into On-Time and disbanded because of user feedback. Unfortunately I am still using my obsolete old-style calendar in this program.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

· @{b}v1.20@{ub} - Third Release (8th June 1996)

   - Program Cataloged.
   - A few minor changes.
   - Was thinking about changing the Calendar to look more like OnTime 2.0 but couldn't be bothered at the moment 8). One idea could be to incorporate the facilities of this program into On-Time. This would solve a few problems. What do you think???

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

· @{b}v1.10@{ub} - Second Release (27th March 1996)

   - Fixed old slider update bug.
   - Fixed CON: deallocation for ARexx messages.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}v1.0@{ub} - Original Release (8th February 1996)

@endnode

